The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Sourav bats for Eden
                                                   Sourav bats for Eden
                      
	Calcutta: Sourav Ganguly on Sunday called for staging IPL matches at the Eden, saying it was a b ig opportunity for Bengal players to showcase their talent. Eden Gardens is a world famous stadium. All attempts should be made to host IPL matches here, the former India captain said at the sidelines of a function.         
	The Calcutta team will have four senior Bengal players. Four under-22 players from the state will also be in the squad. Its a good opportunity for them to showcase their talent on the big stage, he said. (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                       
